  "description": [
    "Tuesday February 25 1919 JUSTICE FOR ERIN PLEA OF GIBBONS AT IRISH MEETING Resolution by Aged Prelate Calls on Wilson to Aid Irish Cause PHILADELPHIA My friends there is liberty in the air The na tions of the earth are clamoring for liberty And why should not freedom loving Ireland join in the general ery With these words Cardinal Gibbons Sunday night presented to the closing session of the convention of the Irish race in America a resolution calling on President Wilson and congress to urge the peace conference to grant Ireland the right of national selfde termination The resolution was adopted unanimously AIGED CARDINALS PLEA Yes said the prelate in his ad dress Ireland wants freedom to breathe the air of heaven She wants freedom to stretch her nrawny and sinewy arms She wants freedom to develop her resources She wants freedom to develop the riches of her soil She wants freedom to carve out her cwn destiny And we are here today to plead the cause of Irelands sons and daughters that they may stand erect redeemed regenerated and disen thralled on their own sacred soil The convention adopted a platform f selfdetermination for Ireland PLEDGE HUGE SUM"
  ],
